-SidePanelCoordinatorTest.SidePanelWidthPreference

# This test fails because our SidePanel doesn't set State::kClosing
-SidePanelCoordinatorTest.OpenWhileClosing

# This test fails because our SidePanel doesn't have header view/resize area
# but it checks these views focus ordern in the panel.
-SidePanelCoordinatorTest.VerifyFocusOrder

# This test fails because our SidePanel doesn't use animation but it checks
# animation state. SidebarContainerView controls panel's animation.
-SidePanelCoordinatorTest.ClosingMidShowFromAnimationReparentsContentView
-SidePanelCoordinatorTest.ShowFromAnimationAnimatesContentViewInTheCorrectDirection_LeftAligned
-SidePanelCoordinatorTest.ShowFromAnimationAnimatesContentViewInTheCorrectDirection_RightAligned
-SidePanelCoordinatorTest.ShowFromAnimationReparentsContentView
-SidePanelCoordinatorTest.ShowFromAnimationReparentsContentViewIfInterruptedByADifferentShowAnimation

# These crash due to what looks like an upstream bug of
# AccessibilityLabelsServiceFactory missing the dependency on
