# This test fails because in HttpsUpgradesInterceptor::MaybeCreateLoader we
# call brave_shields::ShouldUpgradeToHttps, which calls CanUpgradeToHTTPs in
# HttpsUpgradeExceptionsService. But the HttpsUpgradeExceptionsService is not
# ready because it has not loaded exception file from the component and so the
# process of creation of the interceptor's loader gets aborted.
-SimpleWebViewDialogTest.NoHttpsUpgradeOnInitialLoad

# This test fails with multiple errors. Likely has to do with HTTPS upgrade:
# "Mixed Content: The page at 'https://a.com:51799/set-header?Content-Security-Policy:%20frame-src%20*;'
# was loaded over HTTPS, but requested an insecure frame 'http://example.com/'.
# This request has been blocked; the content must be served over HTTPS.",
# source: __const_std::string&_script__ (4).
# In addition, the tests attempts to use CSP like
# {"ftp:*", "ftp://example.com", 0, 0}, which doesn't work correctly because
# "ftp:*" is not getting parsed by CSP parser as a protocol, but as a host (
# because the parser expects :// for parsing it as a protocol). Not sure how/if
# this works upstream.
-ChromeWebPlatformSecurityMetricsBrowserTest.LogCSPFrameSrcWildcardMatchFeature

