# This seems to be an upstream bug. This test crashes in
# extensions::WebViewGuest::FrameNameChanged. The crash happens because the JS
# in chrome/test/data/extensions/platform_apps/web_view/shim/guest_noopener.html
# is using window.open('empty_guest.html', null, 'noopener'); and null is being
# interpreted as an object which somewhere (mojo?) ends up creating a string
# with the value "null" as the frame_name param in CreateNewWindowParams, which
# is not a valid window name and causes a CHECK. Replacing the null in JS with
# undefined makes the test work as expected.
